🖤 𝐑𝐞𝐚𝐝 𝐭𝐡𝐢𝐬 𝐛𝐞𝐟𝐨𝐫𝐞 𝐲𝐨𝐮 𝐜𝐡𝐨𝐨𝐬𝐞 𝐲𝐨𝐮𝐫 𝐜𝐨𝐜𝐤𝐭𝐚𝐢𝐥 𝐩𝐚𝐫𝐭𝐲 𝐦𝐚𝐤𝐞𝐮𝐩 𝐚𝐫𝐭𝐢𝐬𝐭:

𝟏. 𝐆𝐥𝐚𝐦 𝐢𝐬𝐧’𝐭 𝐨𝐧𝐞-𝐬𝐢𝐳𝐞—𝐲𝐨𝐮𝐫𝐬 𝐬𝐡𝐨𝐮𝐥𝐝 𝐛𝐞 𝐦𝐚𝐝𝐞 𝐟𝐨𝐫 𝐲𝐨𝐮:

Your artist should customise the look based on your face shape, skin tone, features, and outfit. If they don’t tailor it to you, that’s a red flag. 🚩 

𝟐. 𝐃𝐞𝐭𝐚𝐢𝐥𝐬 𝐦𝐚𝐤𝐞 𝐭𝐡𝐞 𝐝𝐢𝐟𝐟𝐞𝐫𝐞𝐧𝐜𝐞.:

Your artist should pay attention to the little things—like smooth under-eyes, clean edges, balanced symmetry, and a flawless base. Cocktail glam is all about precision. 💄

𝟑. 𝐋𝐨𝐧𝐠𝐞𝐯𝐢𝐭𝐲 𝐢𝐬 𝐧𝐨𝐧-𝐧𝐞𝐠𝐨𝐭𝐢𝐚𝐛𝐥𝐞:

Your makeup should last through sweat, hugs, photos, and dancing—without turning cakey or oily. A pro knows how to lock it in right using the right products & techniques. 💃🏻 

𝟒. 𝐀 𝐭𝐫𝐮𝐞 𝐌𝐔𝐀 𝐠𝐮𝐢𝐝𝐞𝐬 𝐲𝐨𝐮 𝐛𝐞𝐲𝐨𝐧𝐝 𝐭𝐡𝐞 𝐜𝐡𝐚𝐢𝐫:

Your artist should tell you how to touch up, control sweat, and keep your glam fresh all night. It’s not just about application—it’s about staying power. ✨
.

𝟓 𝐓𝐡𝐢𝐧𝐠𝐬 𝐈’𝐥𝐥 𝐍𝐄𝐕𝐄𝐑 𝐃𝐨 𝐀𝐬 𝐘𝐨𝐮𝐫 𝐌𝐚𝐤𝐞𝐮𝐩 𝐀𝐫𝐭𝐢𝐬𝐭💄❌
	
𝟏. 𝐂𝐨𝐦𝐩𝐫𝐨𝐦𝐢𝐬𝐞 𝐨𝐧 𝐡𝐲𝐠𝐢𝐞𝐧𝐞 – Every brush, sponge, and product is sanitized before it touches your skin. Clean tools, clean hands—non-negotiable.
	
𝟐. 𝐈𝐠𝐧𝐨𝐫𝐞 𝐲𝐨𝐮𝐫 𝐬𝐤𝐢𝐧’𝐬 𝐦𝐨𝐨𝐝 𝐭𝐡𝐚𝐭 𝐝𝐚𝐲 – Whether your skin is dry, oily, or sensitive, I prep it based on how it feels that day, not just your skin type.

𝟑. 𝐏𝐮𝐬𝐡 𝐭𝐫𝐞𝐧𝐝𝐬 𝐭𝐡𝐚𝐭 𝐝𝐨𝐧’𝐭 𝐬𝐮𝐢𝐭 𝐲𝐨𝐮 – Not every viral look is meant for everyone. I’ll never force a trend that doesn’t flatter you.
	
𝟒. 𝐇𝐢𝐝𝐞 𝐲𝐨𝐮𝐫 𝐟𝐞𝐚𝐭𝐮𝐫𝐞𝐬 𝐮𝐧𝐝𝐞𝐫 𝐥𝐚𝐲𝐞𝐫𝐬 – You’ll never feel caked up. I highlight your natural beauty instead of masking it.
	
𝟓. 𝐔𝐬𝐞 𝐥𝐨𝐰-𝐪𝐮𝐚𝐥𝐢𝐭𝐲 𝐨𝐫 𝐞𝐱𝐩𝐢𝐫𝐞𝐝 𝐩𝐫𝐨𝐝𝐮𝐜𝐭𝐬 – I invest in professional, skin-safe products only. No shortcuts, no compromises—your skin deserves the best.
.

Ignore these, regret later — bridal edition✨

1. Be On Time🕰️
Delays = rushed glam. Respect the clock, not just the look.

2. Phones Down 📱❌
No calls, no distractions. Sit still, relax & let the magic happen.

3. Stop Peeking! 👀 
Trust the process. The final reveal is always worth it✨

4. Speak for Yourself 🗣️ 
It’s your face. Don’t let others choose your look.

5. Inspo ≠ Copy 👸🏻 
Inspo pics are great guides, but we’ll customize the look to suit your face.

6. Touch-Ups Matter 💄 
No makeup is invincible — carry your lipstick & blotting paper.
